## Zero-Copy Data Flow Across All Three Tiers

The most important architectural investment is the shared immutable event representation. It eliminates the classic anti-pattern of rebuilding transaction context at every tier boundary.

```
Tier 1 publishes:
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  Arrow Event Buffer (shared memory / mmap)       │
  │  ┌──────────┬──────────┬──────────┬───────────┐  │
  │  │ txn_id   │ features │ scores   │ decision  │  │
  │  │ metadata │ vector   │ per-model│ + reason  │  │
  │  └──────────┴──────────┴──────────┴───────────┘  │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
           │                      │
           ▼                      ▼
     Tier 2 reads              Tier 3 reads
     (no deserialization)      (no deserialization)
     enriches from cache       consumes Tier 2 output
     reasons about decline     dispatches triage actions
```

**Key properties:**

- Tier 1 writes once. Tiers 2 and 3 read by reference.
- No JSON/protobuf rebuild at any boundary.
- Arrow IPC or shared-memory segments enable cross-process zero-copy.
- The same physical bytes feed reasoning, triage, logging, replay, analytics, and offline retraining.

