## Why Sentinel Fits Each Tier

| Tier | Challenge | Sentinel / Helios Capability |
|------|-----------|------------------------------|
| **1** | Tier 1 is not LLM-served, but its GPU branch needs protection | GPU-aware guardrails (NVML/DCGM) monitor the neural scoring GPU; circuit breaker isolates failing replicas |
| **2** | Decline spikes cause burst load on the reasoner | Token admission control + bounded queue; priority lanes for high-value declines |
| **2** | Explanation must start streaming quickly | SSE streaming for fast first-token delivery |
| **3** | Multi-step agent with tool calls is expensive | Helios predicts p99 and chooses accept / queue / degrade; degrade mode produces summary-only output |
| **3** | One noisy triage workflow must not starve others | Per-priority concurrency ceilings; per-tenant token budgets |
| **All** | Need to reconstruct every decision later | `request_id` / `trace_id` correlation across all three tiers; structured logs and traces |

