## GPU-Aware Guardrails Across Tiers

Sentinel's NVML/DCGM polling at < 100 ms intervals applies to both the Tier 1 neural scoring GPU pool and the Tier 2/3 inference GPU pools:

| GPU Signal | Risk | Sentinel Action |
|-----------|------|-----------------|
| `memory.free < 15%` | KV cache OOM for Tier 2/3; inference crash | Throttle admission; no new large-context agents |
| `temperature > 80°C` | Thermal throttling → latency spike → SLA breach | Reduce batch size; alert ops |
| `ECC errors > 0` | Silent data corruption → wrong fraud decision | Drain GPU; circuit-break replica |
| `power.draw > 95% TDP` | Power throttling → unpredictable latency | Cap concurrent requests |
| `Metrics stale > 500 ms` | Blind operation → unknown risk | Deny all new requests (fail-closed) |

The fail-closed posture on stale metrics matches the same philosophy payment processors use for HSM connectivity.

