## Security and Data Handling

- PAN (primary account number) and CVV are **never** included in Arrow event buffers or model prompts. All sensitive fields are tokenized or masked before feature construction.
- Retrieval for Tiers 2 and 3 enforces tenant and role boundaries before any data reaches a model.
- Tool calls and final answers are retained in an immutable audit trail.
- Pinned host memory used by the GPU path is zeroed on arena reset to prevent data leakage across requests.
- PCI-DSS: Sentinel's SSE relay is the natural interception point for PII filtering before tokens reach any downstream consumer.

