## Kubernetes Platform Integration

Separate `ModelDeployment` CRDs per tier ensure workload isolation:

| Tier | GPU Pool | Scaling Basis | Min Replicas |
|------|----------|---------------|-------------|
| **1** (neural scoring) | Dedicated real-time pool | Micro-batch queue depth + GPU duty cycle | 4 (N+1 redundancy) |
| **2** (reasoning) | Near-real-time pool | Sentinel p99 latency + queue depth | 4 |
| **3** (triage) | Batch-tolerant pool | Sentinel p99 latency + queue depth; auto-scales for spikes | 2 |

Black Friday / peak-season scaling: Tier 2 scales 4→16 replicas; Tier 3 scales 2→8. Tier 1 GPU pool scales independently based on transaction volume.

PodDisruptionBudgets ensure N-1 availability during rolling deploys. Graceful drain prevents in-flight requests from being dropped.

