## What Not To Do

- Do not put generative reasoning or large language models in the Tier 1 hot path.
- Do not rebuild transaction context at each tier boundary. Publish once; consume by reference.
- Do not use JSON or protobuf as the internal hot-path data format in Tier 1. Use fixed-layout structs with borrowed references.
- Do not put full transaction payloads in ring buffers. Use compact descriptors.
- Do not use MPMC queues or shared mutable feature maps where SPSC per-core ownership suffices.
- Do not allocate GPU memory per-request. Preallocate everything.
- Do not let Tier 3 batch workloads starve Tier 2 reasoning. Separate GPU pools and token budgets.
- Do not benchmark only average latency. p99 and p999 are the real operational constraints.
- Do not allow raw sensitive records (PAN, CVV) into any Arrow buffer or model prompt.

